# Support-admin zone — the internal STAFF support dashboard on its own subdomain.
#
# The dashboard is cross-tenant (staff view/answer every org's cases). Its ONLY gate is
# Cloudflare Access + the SUPPORT_STAFF_EMAILS allowlist — the same pattern as the Umami
# analytics dashboard. Put a Cloudflare Access application in front of this hostname (Zero
# Trust → Access → Applications) restricted to your staff emails; Access then injects the
# verified identity in the `Cf-Access-Authenticated-User-Email` header, which the app
# trusts (lib/auth/staff.ts). Without an Access app in front, this hostname is UNGATED —
# do not expose it publicly.
#
# OPT-IN self-host template:
#   1. Run a `support-admin` service (the apps/support-admin image) in your compose stack
#      (COMPOSE_PROFILES=admin).
#   2. Copy this file next to the active Caddyfile as `support-admin.caddy`.
#   3. Uncomment `import support-admin*.caddy` in that Caddyfile.
#   4. Replace support-admin.example.com with your real staff subdomain and add the
#      matching Cloudflare Access application.

support-admin.example.com {
	reverse_proxy support-admin:3000
}
